# Changelog

All notable changes to Prayer Times Notifier will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### In Development
- Windows WSL support
- Multiple city support with command-line arguments
- Voice notifications (espeak/festival)
- Web dashboard interface
- Email notification integration
- Quranic ayah display with notifications

---

## [1.1.0] - 01.04.2026

### Added ✨

#### KDE Plasma 6 Support
- Native KDE Plasma 6 integration using `kdialog`
- Automatic desktop environment detection
- System tray notifications with auto-dismiss
- Support for both X11 and Wayland sessions
- Beautiful KDE theming and styling

#### Distribution Support
- **Arch Linux** - Full support with pacman
- **Fedora/RHEL/CentOS** - Complete dnf integration
- **Manjaro** - pacman-based installation
- **Cachy OS** - pacman-based installation  
- **Artix Linux** - pacman and OpenRC support
- **NixOS** - Nix package integration
- **Alpine Linux** - apk package support
- **OpenSUSE** - zypper package support

#### Documentation
- New `DISTRO_GUIDE.md` - Comprehensive distribution-specific installation guide
- New `KDE_PLASMA_GUIDE.md` - Detailed KDE Plasma 6 setup and troubleshooting
- Updated `README.md` with distro installation instructions
- Updated `QUICK_START.md` with multiple distro support

#### Script Improvements
- Enhanced dependency checking with better error messages
- Desktop environment auto-detection
- Fallback notification systems
- Improved error handling and validation
- Better terminal output formatting
- Display detected desktop environment on run

### Changed 🔄

- Unified notification system supporting multiple backends
- More robust API error handling
- Improved crontab examples with environment variables
- Better troubleshooting documentation

### Fixed 🐛

- Notification display on systems without notify-send
- KDE Plasma environment detection issues
- Crontab environment variable handling
- API response validation

---

## [1.0.0] - 31.03.2026

### Initial Release ✨

#### Added
- Initial bash script for prayer time notifications
- Support for Prishtina, Kosovo (optimized for this location)
- Adhan API integration for accurate prayer times
- Desktop notifications using notify-send
- Configurable prayer calculation methods (11 methods supported)
- Timezone configuration support
- Cron job integration guide
- Comprehensive README documentation
- Quick Start guide
- Contributing guidelines
- MIT License

#### Features
- ✅ Fetch current day's prayer times from Adhan API
- ✅ Display all prayer times in terminal
- ✅ Send desktop notifications for prayer times
- ✅ Support for multiple calculation methods
- ✅ Customizable timezone settings
- ✅ Lightweight and minimal dependencies
- ✅ No database required
- ✅ Simple cron job integration

#### Documentation
- README.md with full documentation
- QUICK_START.md for immediate setup
- CONTRIBUTING.md for developers
- Inline code comments and explanations

#### Requirements
- Bash 5.0+
- curl
- jq
- libnotify (notify-send) or kdialog (KDE Plasma)

---

## Version Format

### [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD

**X = Major** (Breaking changes)
**Y = Minor** (New features, backwards compatible)
**Z = Patch** (Bug fixes, backwards compatible)

---

## Types of Changes

- **Added** - New features
- **Changed** - Changes in existing functionality
- **Deprecated** - Soon-to-be removed features
- **Removed** - Now removed features
- **Fixed** - Any bug fixes
- **Security** - Security vulnerability fixes

---

## Release Notes

### How Releases Work
1. Update version in script
2. Update this CHANGELOG.md
3. Create git tag: `git tag -a v1.0.0 -m "Release v1.0.0"`
4. Push tag: `git push origin v1.0.0`
5. Create GitHub Release with release notes

### Version Numbering
- **v1.0.0** - First stable release
- **v1.1.0** - New features added
- **v1.1.1** - Bug fixes
- **v2.0.0** - Major breaking changes

